Books illustrated by Lazzari include the following: 
                        The Man and the Horse, undated; 
                        Nuclear Man, 1954; 
                        The Walking Cross, 1956; and 
                        Important Women of Washington, D.C.: 18 Drawings by Pietro Lazzari, 1961. Other books illustrated by Lazzari include: 
                        New World Writing, by the New American Library, 1953 (with an entry illustrated by Lazzari); 
                        Washington Is Wonderful, by Dorothea Jones, 1956; 
                        Merchants of Labor: The Mexican Bracero Story[autographed] by Ernesto Galarza, 1964.
